<!-- 08 RECENT REPAIRS -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">08, Recent repairs</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">GE jobs from across the territory.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Three representative service calls, model, symptom, diagnosis, repair, and cost. Names and addresses omitted; the technical scenarios are typical of what we see on GE service across each environment.</p>

    <div class="repair-grid">
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>GE Profile PFE28KYNFS French Door, Brentwood</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Display showing "Leak Detected", water dispenser inoperative. Owner had recently replaced the water filter with a third-party generic.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Confirmed third-party filter installed; explained the RPWFE RFID system to the homeowner. Installed genuine GE RPWFE filter; "Leak Detected" did not clear after 2-minute reset. Tested sensor board (WR55X35905), readings off-spec, board failing intermittently.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> RPWFE sensor board replacement with OEM part (in stock on the truck). Verified water dispenser function and filter-life monitoring on full reset. Educated owner on RPWFE-only filter requirement going forward.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost &amp; time:</strong> $245 total. Same-day, completed on the diagnostic visit in 60 minutes.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>GE GTW685BSLWS top-load washer, Rancho Cucamonga</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Washer fills, agitates, but won't enter spin cycle. Cycle progress stalls at the same point every wash.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Lid switch / lid lock fault, common GE top-load failure. Switch ohms-out reading inconsistent, contact intermittent. Drive system tested fine; drain pump tested fine.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Lid switch / lid lock assembly replacement with OEM part. Verified normal lid-lock engagement and full cycle progression on test wash with normal load.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost &amp; time:</strong> $185 total. Same-day, 50 minutes on-site.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>GE Profile PGS930YPFS gas range, Pasadena</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Oven displaying F1 error. Won't reach set temperature; locks itself out approximately 90 seconds after self-clean attempt.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Full breaker reset performed (5 minutes); F1 returned within 30 seconds of power-up. Keypad inspection confirmed no stuck buttons. Temperature sensor ohms-out within spec. Diagnosis: control board watchdog circuit fault, board itself failing.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Oven control board replacement with OEM part (1-day lead from authorized GE distribution; return visit). Verified normal oven operation across bake, broil, and self-clean test cycles. Confirmed F1 cleared.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost &amp; time:</strong> $445 total. Two-visit repair (diagnostic + part install). Total time on-site across both visits: 2 hours 15 minutes.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

